oai_dc:dc.dc:description: DescriptionThis small lovebird, measuringabout 14 em, almost exact! y comparesto the Nyasa lovebird in thesame way as the masked compares tothe Fischer's lovebird. The foreheadis brown and cheeks are brownishblack. Throat and upper breastbecome more orange-red in thebreeding season. Young birds stillbeing fed by their parents also have amore distinctive orange-red upperbreast . The four outer tail feathershave a patch of red. The rest of theplumage is green, darker above andolive green on the neck. Note, uppertail coverts are green, and not paleblue as in the masked lovebirds. Thebill is red and the naked skin aroundthe eyes is white. Legs are grey.
